[[!meta title="Numerous security holes in Tails 0.7.2"]]
[[!pagetemplate template="news.tmpl"]]

[[!tag security/fixed]]

The following security holes affect Tails 0.7.2.

We **strongly** urge you to [[upgrade to Tails 0.8|news/version_0.8]]
as soon as possible in case you are still using an older version.

Details
=======

These are Debian security announces; details can be found on the
[Debian security page](http://security.debian.org/):

  - iceweasel (DSA-2268, DSA-2296)
  - linux-2.6 (DSA-2264, DSA-2303)
  - ca-certificates (DSA-2299)
  - nss (DSA-2300)
  - openssl (DSA-2309)
  - curl (DSA-2271)
  - openoffice.org (DSA-2275)
  - perl (DSA-2265, DSA-2267)
  - libpng (DSA-2287)
  - libsndfile (DSA-2288)
  - libxfont (DSA-2293)
  - freetype (DSA-2294)
